Demos
Video Processing
Whether youre building a live streaming platform and trying to deal with liability / moderation concerns like Twitch / YouTube, or youre in the insurance Application and want to provide feedback to your customers on their driving styles - being able to leverage machine learning to process video content can dramatically reduce overhead and potentially unlock new revenue streams that just werent possible previously.
Leveraging existing Image Classification and Detection Models, trained on ImageNet and Common Objects in Context. Along with FFMpeg we turn a video processing problem into an image processing problem - simple right? Blog post: www.something.com
Image Processing
The bread and butter application or AI, from detection emotional response to stimuli, head counting, to instagram model collaboration scoring - we have the tools and expertise to help you refine your business objectives and help realise ROI.
This algorithm leverages several state-of-the-art object detection models trained on a variety of datasets such as: Common Objects In Context, ImageNet, ALPR, and a variety of proprietary data sources. For more information checkout BlogPost www.example.com
Text Processing
TextBox
Being able to automatically communicate with humans, and to understand what theyre saying is quite powerful. Named Entity Recognition can tell you what someone is asking for (chat bots, support centers) where question answering systems can help automate your support management, they can even help digest legal documents and distill them into things for mere mortals.
Leveraging SpacyIOs Natural Language processing packages, were able to leverage pretrained NLP transformer models (simliar to GPT-X) to be able to gather information automatically from natural language. This kind of system is a necessary first step for any chatbot / human - machine interface.
